"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"Almost from the beginning, risk management has been an important part of a quantitative strategy. Traditional risk management models in quantitative strategies have developed around price-related concepts, such as volatility or hedging.\\n\\nCryptocurrency is a native digital and programmable asset class. This property introduces different risk vectors that have nothing to do with traditional quantitative strategies. Events such as forks (changes in open source software that require users to upgrade to ensure that everyone is running the same version of the code), liquidity attacks, smart contract hacking or new agreement releases, exchange listings, etc. represent the relevant risk dimensions of cryptocurrency assets This should be taken into account in the quantitative strategy. Although cryptocurrencies still lack formal risk management theories that include these new elements, most quantitative models express some personal awareness of them. With the development of cryptocurrency quantitative strategies, its corresponding risk management models will also develop.\",\"timestamp\":1634229098,\"title\":\"The risk model of cryptocurrency\"},\"digest\":\"bGhacaAsfvsXg98LXgrGNVQTnIHCbjMSDLHPS-Stgi0\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0x0DEA89a6C9c14aBFc0f3d048E29084c0b9841B73\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"4JGmd1XB1l9ogC1Dxa-0nPaJUt9fa2PplP6Ojwa84eY\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"Vau3wpYMabob9QrIWKSnVr95FnDQuexJ267TbdATX7U\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"pxx-dWAU5RDDsEmBKA2SECLu2RUc2X0Tm3iIV-hRBVyVtfoTheqxchbMdc2T43gBn_uQ6W1v_GZ0fu6FxoUb4Q\",\"signingKeySignature\":\"0x0185edc654c1d7cf1c82eeaffb1d5ef622e51497d6530ceccac65cc2934a0f4855f7268e80099985f02b01e76eb7873ccc7338fafdbacc7f4a566a74e97b99661b\",\"signingKeyMessage\":\"I authorize publishing on mirror.xyz from this device using:\\n{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\